# OpenGrep/Semgrep ignore list for THIS repository (sscsb's own source tree).
#
# templates/rules/ is the source of the SAST ruleset that sscsb ships. A rule
# file necessarily contains the pattern text it matches on — e.g. the rule that
# flags `npm install` without --ignore-scripts contains the string it looks for —
# so scanning a ruleset with itself produces findings that are false by
# construction. The installed copy (.sscsb/rules) is excluded at the command
# line for the same reason; this covers the source copy that only this repo has.
#
# This is NOT a suppression of a security finding. It stops the scanner from
# analysing its own rule definitions. Nothing under templates/rules/ is executed.
templates/rules/

# Build output.
target/
